<font color="#FF0000">&quot;GOOKS&quot; IS NOW AN OK WORD HERE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Aug  2 19:13:05 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
From The Parking Lot Outback Thread:<br>
         <br>
When I first began posting on this site, in what seems a lifetime ago, last November,I had many ideas and thoughts about Viet Nam and VN Vets. Since then I learned that they were not bums, not schizo's, not panhandling bums on the freeway on ramps with &quot;will work for food' cardboard signs. Instead of I found intelligence, compassion, the free trade of ideas, emotions, and friendship. It was those positive atributes that got me to grow and &quot;transform&quot; and even visit The Wall, let alone  Little Saigon. Alas things change, and not always for the better.<br><br>
In the last month the Fed Up With Spatz thread (47)alone has doubled, and now spews forth with hatred and threats of physical mayhem and violence. Other threads now are dedicated to name calling, insults, and other elementary school yard bully crap. Still more threads are completely self serving. <br><br>
Were I to dial in today, and only read the more recent posts, I would still think that vets were those &quot;on ramp bums&quot;, unfortunately, based on the recent posts. What I read today is the glory of killing &quot;gooks&quot;, the wonderment of bigger and badder weapons, the manly need to make war, and the loss of intellectual discourse. This site has reached the lowest common denominator, and sadly, the other &quot;old&quot; posters are silent. They chose or refuse to confront their brothers, no matter how classless and brash they are. That is too bad. It is a shame and smear on the honor of those<br>
brave enough to be able to share all points of view, not just the limited ones now being posted. <br><br>
From Paul to Cook, Edmond to others, the contribution level has changed. Some say for the better, I think not. When insult replaces emotion, when name calling replaces thinking, when low life scum replace men with honor, change is not for the better. When Viet Nam is replaced with Native American culture, something is wrong with this site. Native American Culture is fine, but not in a discussion of the<br>
history of the War in Viet Nam. Where is the voice or reason, the voice of truth? <br>
Is it hidden and stiffled by the brotherhood of the gun? Has it been trampled by the blood lust of &quot;kill the gooks&quot;? Sadly, the answer is yes.<br><br>
Were it just confined to one thread, to one pow-wow, where the &quot;manly men&quot; could do their over hormone thing, I would welcome it. But, unfortunately, for the silent readership, and those like me, who see no glory in having been a gun totting soldier, &quot;killing gooks&quot; is still a racist expression, and nothing to be proud of. Some of you  older members of this thread seem to think you must embrace anyone because they too served. I think that is wrong. War, just like peace, just like civilian life or military life, is based on character, and class. It has men of honor, and scum of no class. Just because a man has served, and killed, does not bestow upon him character or class. And in the last month, this site has suffered greatly, by the invasion, like a computer virus, of the latter.<br><br>
Can you imagine a Lien, or an Asian posting on this site now, when &quot;killing gooks&quot; is the language of the day, and threats and namecalling have become the morality of the site?  (DocDel, it is far bigger than just me). <br><br>
As for the changes of this site, I truly grieve.<br><br>
Doc Spatz
